summary:
This mod is a ENB profile mixed up with PostProcessInjector with my calibrations.Its calibrated to stay so close to the original Skyrim Atmosphere as possible,
but tune the visuals to get an amazing visual Experience
descriptionHtml:
[center][img]http://kepek.freemail.hu/fototar/kepek/00/03/01/91/18/U0003019118/T00000001332182886388/5384628.jpeg[/img]
[b]Feel-Skyrim-Real.Enb-PostProcessInjector Hybrid [/b]
Please read Description before use it!

[b]Version 1.5 uploaded
-Saturation corrections
-Interior shadow and light corrections
-some fine tuning[/b]

[b]If you like it please don\'t remember to endorse it![/b]

First of all:Sorry for my  bad english!
This mod is a ENB profile mixed up with PostProcessInjector with my calibrations.Its calibrated to stay so close to the original Skyrim Atmosphere as possible,
but tune the visuals to get an amazing visual Experience.This mod was create to my own entertainment but my friends say i should to upload here.
If you like it use it!!!You don\'t like it do not use it!:)
This mod Predecessor was the Breathtaking RCRNENB with vanilla style settings,but now is without RCRN but i recommend to use it.Don\'t worry still fine without RCRN.
See Install part in Description.

There is no FXAA enabled, what bluring the image, and i recommend to not use FXAA.The effects can be disabled with key combinations.
Shift+F12=turn on/off Enb; Pause/Break key=turn on/off PostProcessINJ.
So you can switch to original Skyrim, in game, at any time.

I won\'t lie, this mod is FPS killer and your VGA will hate it :D !
But the visuals pretty nice.
SEE VIDEOS!!!!!!!!!!!!!!

Self maded videos:
[youtube]JJPwNnV-z-k&[/youtube]
[youtube]GJ79n61Zuig&[/youtube]
[youtube]vITCOsuNuZI&[/youtube]
[youtube]c-9uiRg3zwE[/youtube]
[youtube]Q4qhhg4cGGE[/youtube]

-Dark but NOT Pitch Black Nights
-Shiny but not to bright days
-Amazing Dungeons
-Dynamic Depth Of Field
-Ambient Occlusion (optional)
-Easy turn off/on effect, so you can switch to original Skyrim in game, at any time.

INSTALL:

1. Copy all files to Skyrim\'s root folder and overwrite everything if ask.
2. If you want to enable Ambient Occlusion, download the OPTIONAL files and copy all files to Skyrim\'s root folder and overwrite everything if ask.
3. VERY IMPORTANT!In Skyrimprefs.ini(C:Users\\NAME\\Documents\\MyGames\\Skyrim) you need to edit -bFloatPointRenderTarget to 1

[b]For those who want to feel the real experience of this mod i Strongly recommend this:
-First instal RCRN 2.0(Realistic Colors and real nights) Classic Preset[url=http://skyrim.nexusmods.com/downloads/file.php?id=1875] Download here[/url]
-Then copy over my files to Root folder and overwrite it![/b]

	I strongly recommend to edit two more things in Skyrimprefs.ini(C:Users\\NAME\\Documents\\MyGames\\Skyrim):
	
-fGamma=1.10
-fLightLODStartFade=30000.0000

Then make it Read Only.

Strongly Recommended mods:
[url=http://skyrim.nexusmods.com/downloads/file.php?id=9571] Interior Ambient fog Remover[/url]
[url=http://skyrim.nexusmods.com/downloads/file.php?id=9930] Revamped Exterior Fog[/url]

Known Issues:

-If the game won\'t start disable in-game monitoring and diagnostic programs like Afterburner etc.Fraps should be working.

-If you use a third party sunglare mod, the sun would be ugly

-Some dungeons are too bright because the game Define it with \"daytime dungeon\" and ENB configure it as daytime
Sadly this is a Enb issue.Try this mod (far from perfect):[url=http://skyrim.nexusmods.com/downloads/file.php?id=12454]Darker Dungeons ENB[/url]
Otherwise you can decrese the lights in dungeons in the game with \"1+PageDown\" key combination.Press it until it\'s fine for you.
If it\'s too dark you can increase the lights with \"1+PageUP\"

-Some Performance and stability problems.ENB issue too, so don\'t ask me to repair it, because i can\'t :)

CREDITS:
        - Boris Vorontsov creating ENB
	- iolator & Timothy Lottes creating original FXAA PP Injector
        - Eye Adaption Fix Creating GSJ1977
	- Raziel24(On SkyrimNexus:Templar84) settings and fine tuning[/center]
